---
/**
 * distributed-systems/fundamentals · Figure 2 — "timeout is a guess" (Level 1).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component because inline SVG
 * with kebab-case attrs is unreliable in MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Too short a timeout fires false positives and double-runs; too long hangs the system; no correct value exists"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="14" y="30" width="250" height="96" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="139"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a2218">TOO SHORT</text
            >
            <text x="139" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >call a slow node "dead"</text
            >
            <text x="139" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >→ retry runs it twice</text
            >
            <text x="139" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >double charge · split brain</text
            >
            <rect x="296" y="30" width="250" height="96" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="421"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">TOO LONG</text
            >
            <text x="421" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >hang on a dead node</text
            >
            <text x="421" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >→ slow detection</text
            >
            <text x="421" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >cascading queues</text
            >
            <text
                x="280"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">no provably-correct N — the network has no upper delay bound</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A real network is <em>asynchronous</em>: no guaranteed bound on message delay or pause
        length. With no bound, no timeout can ever be provably correct. (DDIA Ch. 8, "Timeouts and
        Unbounded Delays.")
    </figcaption>
</figure>
